rComments: Has amazing connections in Ottawa and across Canadawidely respected. He was able to secure me a very successful tech law internship placement in Ottawa for one semester and I learned a ton. Really wants to help and inspire students and see them reach their full potential. Thank you for your mentorship!

Inspiring professor and one of the most famous law profs at uOttawa/in Canada. Has won the Top 25 Lawyers in Canada several  years in a row for good reason. Highly recommended and very inspiring speaker.

I do not agree that this professor is boring or disengaging. He is extremely knowledgable and world-renowned and the current Canada Research Chair in Internet and E-Commerce Law. Very sought-after speaker because of his sharp acumen and public speaking skills. Passionate. Mentors and supports students. Highly recommended!
Very interesting, very knowledgable, and really passionate about the subject he teaches. I don't ge technology at all and my Regulation of Internet Commerce class is amazing, highly recommended!
Boring speaker. Has a major ego. Discusses examples instead of legal principles. Has a very one-sided perspective on topics.
